In the mysterious, RPG dungeon-like Tower, Confucius Kim lives a mundane existence, envying all the star hunters. One day, his wish for more is granted with a legendary skill to copy others’ abilities… at the cost of his life. Before he can make sense of it, he’s killed by the #1 hunter, the Flame Emperor! But this activates his skill and now he’s copied a new one, the ability to travel back in time upon death. How will Confucius use these skills to outplay the competition and rise to the top?
(Source: Tapas)

Mikhail Walpurgis didn't feel qualified for the title of Hero, and instead let the warrior Siegfried lead the prophesied battle against the Devil. But after Siegfried dies and the army is defeated, Mikhail has one last move before the end of the world. And so he turns back time. Now, Mikhail has the chance to reclaim the title he gave up and save everyone. The only problem is, no one believes the prophecy about the war! Can Mikhail manage to gather an army and make this life count?
(Source: Tapas)
